I"æ<p>The <code>geonetnz_volcano</code> integration lets you use a GeoJSON feed provided by
New Zealandâ€™s <a href="https://www.geonet.org.nz/">GeoNet</a> with information
about volcanoes in the New Zealand region.
It shows information of those volcanoes filtered by distance to Home Assistantâ€™s
location.</p>
<p>Entities are generated and updated automatically with each update
from the feed. Each entity defines the <a href="https://www.geonet.org.nz/about/volcano/val">volcanic alert level</a>
as its state.  Latitude and longitude of the volcano are included as attributes
to show on the default map automatically.</p>
<p>The data is updated every 5 minutes.</p>
